. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ganache"},{"content":"Place peanuts into mixing bowl and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add remaining ingredients and cook <b>5 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Blend <b>30 sec\/speed 8<b>, then transfer into a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Place frozen ice cream cubes into mixing bowl and blend <b>1 min\/speed 7<b>, with aid of spatula."},{"content":"Transfer half of the ice cream into a loaf tin (25 x 10 x 11 cm). Top with half of the ganache, and repeat layering with remaining half of the ice cream and ganache. Place into freezer until firm. Before serving, remove ice cream from freezer and leave for 5 minutes before scooping into waffle cones or serving bowls."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For a dinner party, you can serve this ice cream in slices by briefly placing loaf tin under hot tap water, then turning out onto a chopping board or serving platter and slicing as desired.","Instead of ice cube trays, you can freeze the ice cream mixture in a shallow freezable storage container."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","24h 40m","8 portions"]}